  - q: "What is the Yi Jing (I Ching)?"
    a: "The Yi Jing (易經), or Book of Changes, is one of the oldest Chinese classical texts, dating back over 3,000 years. It is both a divination manual and a philosophical treatise that models the dynamic patterns of change in the universe through 64 hexagrams composed of yin and yang lines."
  - q: "What are the 64 hexagrams?"
    a: "The 64 hexagrams are figures composed of six horizontal lines, each either solid (yang) or broken (yin). They are formed by stacking two trigrams (three-line figures). Each hexagram represents a specific archetypal situation and includes judgements and line texts describing its meaning."
