    <section id="hexagrams">
<div class="lang-en">
      <h2>The 64 Hexagrams</h2>
      <p>By stacking two trigrams &mdash; a lower (inner) trigram and an upper (outer) trigram &mdash; 64 hexagrams are generated. Each hexagram consists of six lines numbered from bottom to top. The lower trigram represents the internal situation; the upper represents the external or future development.</p>
      <p>Each hexagram carries:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>A name</strong> &mdash; e.g., Hexagram 1 Qian (<span class="chinese-char">乾</span>, The Creative), Hexagram 2 Kun (<span class="chinese-char">坤</span>, The Receptive)</li>
        <li><strong>A judgement (<span class="chinese-char">卦辭</span>)</strong> &mdash; The overall meaning attributed to King Wen</li>
        <li><strong>Line texts (<span class="chinese-char">爻辭</span>)</strong> &mdash; Specific meanings for each of the six positions</li>
        <li><strong>Image commentary (<span class="chinese-char">象傳</span>)</strong> &mdash; A metaphor drawn from nature explaining the hexagram's dynamics</li>
      </ul>
      <p>The 64 hexagrams represent every archetypal situation a person or society can encounter &mdash; from creative breakthrough (Hexagram 1) to completion and renewal (Hexagram 63 and 64). They are not static symbols but dynamic models of situations in the process of change.</p>
</div>
<div class="lang-tc">
      <h2>六十四卦</h2>
      <p>將兩個經卦——下卦（內卦）與上卦（外卦）——相疊，便得六十四別卦。每卦由六爻組成，自下而上編號。下卦象徵內在情境，上卦象徵外部環境或未來走向。</p>
      <p>每一卦包含：</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>卦名</strong> &mdash; 如第一卦乾（<span class="chinese-char">乾</span>），第二卦坤（<span class="chinese-char">坤</span>）</li>
        <li><strong>卦辭（<span class="chinese-char">卦辭</span>）</strong> &mdash; 相傳為周文王所繫之總體判斷</li>
        <li><strong>爻辭（<span class="chinese-char">爻辭</span>）</strong> &mdash; 六個爻位各自的具體含義</li>
        <li><strong>象傳（<span class="chinese-char">象傳</span>）</strong> &mdash; 取自自然之象，闡釋該卦的動態意涵</li>
      </ul>
      <p>六十四卦涵蓋了個人或社會可能遭遇的所有典型情境——從創生開拓（第一卦）到功成更始（第六十三、六十四卦）。它們並非靜止的符號，而是處於變化過程中的動態模型。</p>
</div>
<div class="lang-sc">
      <h2>六十四卦</h2>
      <p>将两个经卦——下卦（内卦）与上卦（外卦）——相叠，便得六十四别卦。每卦由六爻组成，自下而上编号。下卦象征内在情境，上卦象征外部环境或未来走向。</p>
      <p>每一卦包含：</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>卦名</strong> &mdash; 如第一卦乾（<span class="chinese-char">乾</span>），第二卦坤（<span class="chinese-char">坤</span>）</li>
        <li><strong>卦辞（<span class="chinese-char">卦辭</span>）</strong> &mdash; 相传为周文王所系之总体判断</li>
        <li><strong>爻辞（<span class="chinese-char">爻辭</span>）</strong> &mdash; 六个爻位各自的具体含义</li>
        <li><strong>象传（<span class="chinese-char">象傳</span>）</strong> &mdash; 取自自然之象，阐释该卦的动态意涵</li>
      </ul>
      <p>六十四卦涵盖了个人或社会可能遭遇的所有典型情境——从创生开拓（第一卦）到功成更始（第六十三、六十四卦）。它们并非静止的符号，而是处于变化过程中的动态模型。</p>
</div>
    </section>

    <section id="divination">
<div class="lang-en">
      <h2>Methods of Divination</h2>
      <p><strong>The Yarrow Stalk Method (<span class="chinese-char">蓍草法</span>)</strong> is the oldest and most traditional approach. Using 50 yarrow stalks (one set aside, 49 manipulated), the diviner performs a series of divisions and counts, repeated 18 times to generate six lines. This method produces four possible line types: old yin, young yin, young yang, and old yang &mdash; with the "old" lines being changing lines that transform into their opposites.</p>
      <p><strong>The Three Coin Method (<span class="chinese-char">三錢法</span>)</strong> emerged during the Han Dynasty as a simplified alternative. Three coins are tossed six times; heads and tails values are summed to determine each line. While faster, the probability distribution differs from the yarrow stalk method, giving changing lines a higher frequency.</p>
      <p>When changing lines appear, a second hexagram is generated showing the situation's direction of transformation. The reading is drawn from both the primary and transformed hexagrams, with the changing lines receiving particular interpretive emphasis.</p>
</div>
<div class="lang-tc">
      <h2>占筮方法</h2>
      <p><strong>蓍草法（<span class="chinese-char">蓍草法</span>）</strong>是最古老、最正統的占筮方式。取蓍草五十策（虛一不用，實用四十九），經過分二、掛一、揲四、歸奇等步驟，反覆十八變以成六爻。此法可得四種爻象：老陰、少陰、少陽、老陽——其中「老」爻即動爻，會變化為其對立面。</p>
      <p><strong>三錢法（<span class="chinese-char">三錢法</span>）</strong>始於漢代，為蓍草法的簡化替代方案。擲三枚銅錢六次，依正反面數值之和判定各爻。此法雖更便捷，但其概率分佈與蓍草法有所不同，動爻出現的頻率較高。</p>
      <p>當出現動爻時，卦象隨之變化，生成第二卦（之卦），顯示情勢的演變方向。解卦時需同時參照本卦與之卦，動爻所在的爻位尤受重視。</p>
</div>
<div class="lang-sc">
      <h2>占筮方法</h2>
      <p><strong>蓍草法（<span class="chinese-char">蓍草法</span>）</strong>是最古老、最正统的占筮方式。取蓍草五十策（虚一不用，实用四十九），经过分二、挂一、揲四、归奇等步骤，反复十八变以成六爻。此法可得四种爻象：老阴、少阴、少阳、老阳——其中"老"爻即动爻，会变化为其对立面。</p>
      <p><strong>三钱法（<span class="chinese-char">三錢法</span>）</strong>始于汉代，为蓍草法的简化替代方案。掷三枚铜钱六次，依正反面数值之和判定各爻。此法虽更便捷，但其概率分布与蓍草法有所不同，动爻出现的频率较高。</p>
      <p>当出现动爻时，卦象随之变化，生成第二卦（之卦），显示情势的演变方向。解卦时需同时参照本卦与之卦，动爻所在的爻位尤受重视。</p>
</div>
    </section>

    <section id="ten-wings">
<div class="lang-en">
      <h2>The Ten Wings (<span class="chinese-char">十翼</span>)</h2>
      <p>The Ten Wings are philosophical commentaries traditionally attributed to Confucius, appended to the core hexagram text. They elevate the Yi Jing from a divination manual to a comprehensive cosmological philosophy:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Tuan Zhuan (<span class="chinese-char">彖傳</span>)</strong> &mdash; Commentary on the hexagram judgements (2 sections)</li>
        <li><strong>Xiang Zhuan (<span class="chinese-char">象傳</span>)</strong> &mdash; Commentary on the images and individual lines (2 sections)</li>
        <li><strong>Xi Ci Zhuan (<span class="chinese-char">繫辭傳</span>)</strong> &mdash; The "Great Treatise," the most philosophically important commentary, discussing cosmology, the nature of change, and the purpose of divination (2 sections)</li>
        <li><strong>Wen Yan Zhuan (<span class="chinese-char">文言傳</span>)</strong> &mdash; Commentary on the first two hexagrams (Qian and Kun)</li>
        <li><strong>Shuo Gua Zhuan (<span class="chinese-char">說卦傳</span>)</strong> &mdash; Discussion of the trigrams and their attributes</li>
        <li><strong>Xu Gua Zhuan (<span class="chinese-char">序卦傳</span>)</strong> &mdash; Explanation of the hexagram sequence</li>
        <li><strong>Za Gua Zhuan (<span class="chinese-char">雜卦傳</span>)</strong> &mdash; Contrasting hexagram pairs</li>
      </ul>
</div>
<div class="lang-tc">
      <h2>十翼（<span class="chinese-char">十翼</span>）</h2>
      <p>十翼是附於卦爻辭之後的哲學性傳注，傳統上歸為孔子所作。十翼使易經從占筮之書升格為體系完備的宇宙論哲學著作：</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>彖傳（<span class="chinese-char">彖傳</span>）</strong> &mdash; 解釋卦辭之義（上、下二篇）</li>
        <li><strong>象傳（<span class="chinese-char">象傳</span>）</strong> &mdash; 解釋卦象及各爻之義（上、下二篇）</li>
        <li><strong>繫辭傳（<span class="chinese-char">繫辭傳</span>）</strong> &mdash; 又稱「大傳」，為十翼中哲學意涵最為深厚的篇章，論述宇宙論、變化之理與占筮之目的（上、下二篇）</li>
        <li><strong>文言傳（<span class="chinese-char">文言傳</span>）</strong> &mdash; 專釋乾、坤二卦</li>
        <li><strong>說卦傳（<span class="chinese-char">說卦傳</span>）</strong> &mdash; 論述八卦的性質與取象</li>
        <li><strong>序卦傳（<span class="chinese-char">序卦傳</span>）</strong> &mdash; 闡明六十四卦的排列次序</li>
        <li><strong>雜卦傳（<span class="chinese-char">雜卦傳</span>）</strong> &mdash; 以對舉之法辨析各卦異同</li>
      </ul>
</div>
<div class="lang-sc">
      <h2>十翼（<span class="chinese-char">十翼</span>）</h2>
      <p>十翼是附于卦爻辞之后的哲学性传注，传统上归为孔子所作。十翼使易经从占筮之书升格为体系完备的宇宙论哲学著作：</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>彖传（<span class="chinese-char">彖傳</span>）</strong> &mdash; 解释卦辞之义（上、下二篇）</li>
        <li><strong>象传（<span class="chinese-char">象傳</span>）</strong> &mdash; 解释卦象及各爻之义（上、下二篇）</li>
        <li><strong>系辞传（<span class="chinese-char">繫辭傳</span>）</strong> &mdash; 又称"大传"，为十翼中哲学意涵最为深厚的篇章，论述宇宙论、变化之理与占筮之目的（上、下二篇）</li>
        <li><strong>文言传（<span class="chinese-char">文言傳</span>）</strong> &mdash; 专释乾、坤二卦</li>
        <li><strong>说卦传（<span class="chinese-char">說卦傳</span>）</strong> &mdash; 论述八卦的性质与取象</li>
        <li><strong>序卦传（<span class="chinese-char">序卦傳</span>）</strong> &mdash; 阐明六十四卦的排列次序</li>
        <li><strong>杂卦传（<span class="chinese-char">雜卦傳</span>）</strong> &mdash; 以对举之法辨析各卦异同</li>
      </ul>
</div>
    </section>

    <section id="philosophy">
<div class="lang-en">
      <h2>Philosophical Significance</h2>
      <p>The Yi Jing's influence on Chinese thought is immeasurable. It established foundational concepts that permeate all Chinese intellectual traditions:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Yin-Yang (<span class="chinese-char">陰陽</span>)</strong> &mdash; All phenomena arise from the interplay of complementary opposites</li>
        <li><strong>Cyclical change</strong> &mdash; The universe moves in recurring patterns; decline contains the seed of renewal</li>
        <li><strong>Resonance (<span class="chinese-char">感應</span>)</strong> &mdash; Corresponding elements in different domains of reality respond to each other</li>
        <li><strong>Timely action (<span class="chinese-char">時</span>)</strong> &mdash; Wisdom lies in recognising and harmonising with the present moment's potential</li>
      </ul>
      <p>The Yi Jing directly shaped <a href="/wuxing/">Wu Xing theory</a>, Chinese medicine, <a href="/fengshui/">feng shui</a>, <a href="/bazi/">BaZi</a>, <a href="/qimen/">Qi Men Dun Jia</a>, and even Chinese governance philosophy. Leibniz famously saw in its binary structure a precursor to his own binary number system.</p>
</div>
<div class="lang-tc">
      <h2>哲學意義</h2>
      <p>易經對中國思想的影響無可估量。它所確立的基本觀念滲透於中華一切學術傳統之中：</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>陰陽（<span class="chinese-char">陰陽</span>）</strong> &mdash; 萬象皆生於相反相成之兩極的交互作用</li>
        <li><strong>循環變化</strong> &mdash; 宇宙依循週而復始的規律運行；衰落之中已孕育新生之機</li>
        <li><strong>感應（<span class="chinese-char">感應</span>）</strong> &mdash; 不同領域中相對應的事物彼此呼應、交感</li>
        <li><strong>時中（<span class="chinese-char">時</span>）</strong> &mdash; 智慧在於體察當下時機的潛能，並與之相應而行</li>
      </ul>
      <p>易經直接影響了<a href="/wuxing/">五行學說</a>、中醫、<a href="/fengshui/">風水</a>、<a href="/bazi/">八字</a>、<a href="/qimen/">奇門遁甲</a>，乃至中國的治國哲學。萊布尼茨曾從易經的二進位結構中，看到了他自身二進制數學體系的先聲。</p>
</div>
<div class="lang-sc">
      <h2>哲学意义</h2>
      <p>易经对中国思想的影响无可估量。它所确立的基本观念渗透于中华一切学术传统之中：</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>阴阳（<span class="chinese-char">陰陽</span>）</strong> &mdash; 万象皆生于相反相成之两极的交互作用</li>
        <li><strong>循环变化</strong> &mdash; 宇宙依循周而复始的规律运行；衰落之中已孕育新生之机</li>
        <li><strong>感应（<span class="chinese-char">感應</span>）</strong> &mdash; 不同领域中相对应的事物彼此呼应、交感</li>
        <li><strong>时中（<span class="chinese-char">時</span>）</strong> &mdash; 智慧在于体察当下时机的潜能，并与之相应而行</li>
      </ul>
      <p>易经直接影响了<a href="/wuxing/">五行学说</a>、中医、<a href="/fengshui/">风水</a>、<a href="/bazi/">八字</a>、<a href="/qimen/">奇门遁甲</a>，乃至中国的治国哲学。莱布尼茨曾从易经的二进位结构中，看到了他自身二进制数学体系的先声。</p>
</div>
    </section>
